---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { META } from "../lib/catalog";

const generatedDate = new Date(META.generated_at).toLocaleString();
---

<Layout title="About">
  <article class="about">
    <h1>About this archive</h1>

    <p>
      An independent research catalog of the
      <strong>Whitney Museum of American Art's</strong> public collection,
      built from the museum's
      <a href="https://github.com/whitneymuseum/open-access" rel="noopener">open-access archive</a>
      (released under CC0) and its public REST
      <a href="https://whitney.org/about/website/api" rel="noopener">API</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      The site mirrors {META.counts.artworks.toLocaleString()} artworks
      attributed to {META.counts.artists_with_works.toLocaleString()} artists,
      with metadata refreshed regularly. Each artwork has its own page; you can
      filter by classification, browse by artist, and search across titles
      and media.
    </p>

    <h2>What's in the data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Artwork title, artist(s), display date, classification, medium, dimensions, credit line.</li>
      <li>Accession number and parsed acquisition year (when derivable from the prefix).</li>
      <li>Image references — hot-linked to <code>whitneymedia.org</code>; no images are re-hosted here.</li>
      <li>Exhibitions per artist (artwork-level exhibition history isn't published).</li>
      <li>On-view status, when known.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Methodology</h2>
    <p>
      Two data sources feed the catalog: the museum's CC0-licensed CSV
      (collection-only artworks, minimal fields) and the public API (deeper
      metadata including biographies, ULAN/Wikidata IDs, descriptions,
      images, and biennial flags). Where they differ, the API record is
      taken as the canonical grain — the CSV flattens portfolio works
      (e.g., a 155-print portfolio appears as 155 rows in CSV but 1 record
      in the API). The CSV's reproduction-credit field is merged in where
      present.
    </p>

    <h2>Licensing</h2>
    <p>
      This is an <strong>independent research project</strong>, not affiliated
      with or endorsed by the Whitney Museum of American Art. Built by
      <a href="https://frsantos.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ryan Santos</a>.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Open-access CSV data: <strong>CC0 1.0</strong>
        — public domain.
      </li>
      <li>
        API-derived metadata and images: noncommercial / educational use with
        attribution. Images are served from <code>whitneymedia.org</code> and
        are not redistributed.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p class="generated">
      Data snapshot generated <time>{generatedDate}</time>.
      Source pipeline:
      <a href="https://github.com/whitneymuseum/open-access" rel="noopener">whitneymuseum/open-access</a>
      + <a href="https://whitney.org/about/website/api" rel="noopener">whitney.org/about/website/api</a>.
    </p>
  </article>

  <style>
    .about { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .about h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
    .about h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
    .about p { line-height: 1.6; }
    .about ul { line-height: 1.7; padding-left: 1.25rem; }
    .about .generated {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      padding-top: 1rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
